                              <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapse-21" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapse-18">Are the websites all .com versions?</button>
                          </div>
                          <div id="collapse-21" class="accordion-collapse collapse " aria-labelledby="collapse-item-21" data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion">
                              <div class="accordion-body">
                                  <p class="faq-text">We have an extensive list of .com news sites, but we also work with a number of international subsidiaries. We have different arrangements with different websites. Some are .com, others are country specific subsidiary sites. Please ask prior to publication if you have questions about whether a website is on the .com or a subsidiary site. <br>

                                      The global news sites, while mostly skewed toward the US, can be either .com, or country specific subsidiary sites, depending on what we have in our inventory. Our inventory changes often so we cannot provide an exhaustive list so if you are concerned about the format of a news site’s URL, domain, or sub-domain, or worried about where on the site your article or news story will appear, please ask us prior to publication. </p>
                              </div>
                          </div>
                      </div>
                      <div class="accordion-card style2">
                          <div class="accordion-header" id="collapse-item-22">
                              <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapse-22" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapse-22">Can I talk to you about how my article will look and where it will appear before publication?</button>
                          </div>
                          <div id="collapse-22" class="accordion-collapse collapse " aria-labelledby="collapse-item-22" data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion">
                              <div class="accordion-body">
                                  <p class="faq-text">It is your right to ask questions about the news site prior to publication, and we will do our best to answer any questions you might have. If in doubt, please ask prior to publication. Once published, we cannot do anything to change the article, content, language, links (follow or no-follow) or any other details you might have an issue with, if we don’t know of that issue in advance. </p>
                              </div>
                          </div>
                      </div>
                      <div class="accordion-card style2">
                          <div class="accordion-header" id="collapse-item-23">
                              <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapse-23" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapse-18">Yahoo Finance, Business Insider, Associated Press & Bloomberg</button>
                          </div>
                          <div id="collapse-23" class="accordion-collapse collapse " aria-labelledby="collapse-item-23" data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion">
                              <div class="accordion-body">
                                  <p class="faq-text">These websites require news stories written in the style of a press release announcing a corporate milestone, notable hire or other achievement. There are special editorial requirements that apply. For example, you cannot be promoting an individual or blockchain project for example. </p>
                              </div>
                          </div>
                      </div>
                      <div class="accordion-card style2">
                          <div class="accordion-header" id="collapse-item-24">
                              <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapse-24" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapse-18">Forbes</button>
                          </div>
                          <div id="collapse-24" class="accordion-collapse collapse " aria-labelledby="collapse-item-24" data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion">
                              <div class="accordion-body">
                                  <p class="faq-text">We will deliver a full feature in Forbes Georgia or Israel (through our brand voice partnership), which still rank in the US. </p>
                              </div>
                          </div>
                      </div>
                      <div class="accordion-card style2">
                          <div class="accordion-header" id="collapse-item-25">
                              <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapse-25" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapse-25">Vogue</button>
                          </div>
                          <div id="collapse-25" class="accordion-collapse collapse " aria-labelledby="collapse-item-25" data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion">
                              <div class="accordion-body">
                                  <p class="faq-text">We will deliver a full feature in a subsidiary publication of Vogue Magazine online in English. Please note that a feature in Vogue is an upgrade available on the Yearly, Quarterly or Monthly subscriptions (but not the Basic subscription), but you are required to pay a one off additional $1,500 in the month you want to secure the placement. </p>
                              </div>
                          </div>
                      </div>
                      <div class="accordion-card style2">
                          <div class="accordion-header" id="collapse-item-26">
                              <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapse-26" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapse-26">Fashion Publications</button>
                          </div>
                          <div id="collapse-26" class="accordion-collapse collapse " aria-labelledby="collapse-item-26" data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion">
                              <div class="accordion-body">
                                  <p class="faq-text">The majority of our fashion publications are US based although some of our most popular publications are via international subsidiaries, which mostly rank in the US. In particular, Elle, Vogue, Harper’s Bazaar, GQ, Glamour, L’Officiel and Marie Claire are published via international subsidiaries. They all rank strongly in the United States. </p>
                              </div>
                          </div>
                      </div>
                      <div class="accordion-card style2">
                          <div class="accordion-header" id="collapse-item-27">
                              <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapse-27" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapse-27">Prohibited Topics: Topics we do not write about</button>
                          </div>
                          <div id="collapse-27" class="accordion-collapse collapse " aria-labelledby="collapse-item-27" data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion">
                              <div class="accordion-body">
                                  <p class="faq-text">We do not write about the following topics:</p>
                                  <ul class="faq-text">
                                      <li>Misleading or Deceptive Information: Content that is knowingly false or misleading, including fake news or hoaxes.</li>
                                      <li>Offensive or Inappropriate Content: Material that is offensive, discriminatory, or inappropriate, including hate speech, derogatory language, or content promoting violence or intolerance.</li>
                                      <li>Illegal Activities: Any content that promotes illegal activities or provides instructions on engaging in illegal actions.</li>
                                      <li>Personal and Confidential Information: Publishing personal, confidential, or proprietary information without consent, such as private contact details, financial data, or trade secrets.</li>
                                      <li>Medical and Health Claims: Unsupported or non-compliant medical claims, especially those related to miracle cures, unapproved drugs, or misleading health advice.</li>
                                      <li>Financial and Investment Advice: Content offering specific financial or investment advice without proper disclaimers or that could be considered as misleading financial promotions.</li>
                                      <li>Adult Content: Adult content or pornography is generally prohibited.</li>
                                      <li>Political or Religious Bias: Some PR distribution sites may avoid overtly political or religious content, especially if it’s controversial or extremist in nature.</li>
                                      <li>Spam and Irrelevant Content: Material that is considered spam, overly promotional without substantive information, or irrelevant to the intended audience.</li>
                                      <li>Libelous, Defamatory or Slanderous Material: Content that could be considered libelous, slanderous, or defamatory.</li>
                                  </ul>
                                  <p>If you purchase one of our services and intend us to write about any of these topics. we will substitute these topics for permitted topics, but we will not issue a refund. </p>
                              </div>
                          </div>
                      </div>
                      <div class="accordion-card style2">
                          <div class="accordion-header" id="collapse-item-28">
                              <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapse-28" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapse-28">Unused News Stories Expire After 1 Year</button>
                          </div>
                          <div id="collapse-28" class="accordion-collapse collapse " aria-labelledby="collapse-item-28" data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion">
                              <div class="accordion-body">
                                  <p class="faq-text">Upon engaging our services, either through a one-off campaign or a retainer agreement, clients are allocated a specific number of news stories, as detailed in their individual service agreement.

                                      Subject to our refund policy, it is understood and agreed upon by you that any unused news stories allocated under either a one-off campaign or a retainer agreement must be utilized within one (1) year from the date of engagement with The Neuralnest, or, in the case of retainer clients, within one (1) year from the date of the final payment made under their retainer agreement.</p>
                              </div>
                          </div>
                      </div>
                      <div class="accordion-card style2">
                          <div class="accordion-header" id="collapse-item-29">
                              <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapse-29" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapse-29">Visa Publicity</button>
                          </div>
                          <div id="collapse-29" class="accordion-collapse collapse " aria-labelledby="collapse-item-29" data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion">
                              <div class="accordion-body">
                                  <ul class="faq-text">
                                      <li>No Representation That Applicant Will Be Granted a Visa: The Neuralnest makes no representations that the client will be granted a visa. Our guarantee merely extends to the publication of stories that can help applicants prove their extraordinary notability.</li>
                                      <li>Draft Article Revisions: The Neuralnest agrees to perform up to one complete rewrite of any article at the request of the client, without additional charge. Should the client request any further complete revisions or rewrites beyond the initial complimentary revision, such requests will be subject to a fee of $200 per revision which is payable via this secure link.</li>
                                      <li>Time Sensitive Requests: Clients requesting that we publish articles within a 4-week timeline will be subject to a “rush fee” of $500 per article. Rush fees are payable via this secure payment link.</li>
                                      <li>The Neuralnest specializes in the creation of articles intended for submission to the United States Citizenship and Immigration Services (USCIS) as evidence of the beneficiary’s original contributions of major significance in the fields of science, scholarship, art, athletics, or business, pertinent to EB-1A petitions. Our service includes the provision of articles published in reputable global publications, serving as objective documentary evidence of the beneficiary’s significant contributions to their respective field. These published articles aim to demonstrate that the beneficiary’s contributions have elicited widespread public commentary and acknowledgment within their field. However, The Neuralnest’s scope of services does not extend to providing documentary evidence of the beneficiary’s recognition by peers within their field of expertise.</li>
                                      <li>Specifically, we do not furnish
                                          <ul>
                                              <li>Testimonies or support letters from experts that elaborate on the beneficiary’s major significant contributions.</li>
                                              <li>Letter from the publications outlining their selection process and criteria.</li>
                                              <li>Documentation evidencing the implementation of the beneficiary’s work by others, which may include, but is not limited to:</li>
                                              <li>Contracts with entities utilizing the beneficiary’s products or services.</li>
                                              <li>Usage of licensed technology by third parties.</li>
                                              <li>Patents that are actively employed and recognized as significant within the beneficiary’s field</li>
                                          </ul>
                                      </li>
                                  </ul>
                              </div>
                          </div>
                      </div>
                      <div class="accordion-card style2">
                          <div class="accordion-header" id="collapse-item-30">
                              <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapse-30" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapse-30">Agencies & White Labelling</button>
                          </div>
                          <div id="collapse-30" class="accordion-collapse collapse " aria-labelledby="collapse-item-30" data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion">
                              <div class="accordion-body">
                                  <p class="faq-text">These are the terms and conditions that apply to agencies. </p>
                                  <ol class="faq-text">
                                      <li>Collaboration on Content: You and The Neuralnest will collaborate on planning and approving the placement of your articles and TV segments. You must approve these placements in advance.</li>
                                      <li>No Guarantees on Placements: The Neuralnest cannot guarantee specific placements or the availability of a certain number of placements that meet your requirements.</li>
                                      <li>Creative Control and Revisions: Both parties have mutual approval rights over all content created. However, media outlets might modify this content, and The Neuralnest isn’t liable for these changes.</li>
                                      <li>Right to Reject or Terminate: The Neuralnest can reject any content or end placements at its discretion if it believes the content poses legal, financial, or reputation risks or violates media policies.</li>
                                      <li>Change Requests: You can request changes to the scope of work at your own expense. Changes must be mutually agreed upon in writing.</li>
                                      <li>Fees: You must pay The Neuralnest for its services as outlined on their website or as notified. Non-payment constitutes a breach of agreement.</li>
                                      <li>Confidentiality: You agree to keep all proprietary information confidential unless you have written permission from The Neuralnest to share it.</li>
                                      <li>Intellectual Property: The Neuralnest retains rights to any materials it creates. You grant The Neuralnest a non-exclusive license to use your creative materials and trademarks for the purpose of securing placements.</li>
                                      <li>Termination: The Neuralnest can end the agreement for any reason or if you breach the terms. You are responsible for all fees due up to the termination date.</li>
                                      <li>Writing: The Agency subscription is exclusive of our writing service. If you require us to write and edit stories for your clients, each story is $100 USD (up to 600 words), and includes one round of edits. The link to purchase is here. </li>
                                      <li>Legal Compliance and Dispute Resolution: You agree to comply with all applicable laws and resolve any disputes through mediation or arbitration in the British Virgin Islands.</li>
                                      <li>Limitations: The Neuralnest disclaims all warranties and limits its liability for damages. You are responsible for your own use of the website and services.</li>
                                  </ol>
                              </div>
                          </div>
                      </div>

                  </div>
              </div>
          </div>
      </div>
  </div>

